<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,222,1326]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,366,391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax longer than abdomen; pseudorostrum long; antennal notch obvious and broad, reaching considerably backwards beyond the anterior margin of the frontal lobe; middorsal crista serrulated, reaching with a short posterior interruption the hind margin of carapace; two teeth on each lateral side of the frontal lobe: one close to the margin and one on the posterior part; additional tooth on the posterior part of the pseudorostral lobe.
</paragraph>
